# 1. 圧倒される歌声

Shiho: I think I'll be on my way now. If you'll excuse me.
Manager: Sure, and thanks for your hard work today. Say, isn't your solo show coming up? How's the prep going?
Shiho: We're doing everything we can to be ready. The closer we get to the day of, the more focused we feel.
Shiho: It's like... We give each other energy just by picking up our instruments together.
Manager: I see. That's exciting to hear. Are you off to practice now?
Shiho: Actually, no. My amp started acting up yesterday, so I'm taking it to be fixed.
Manager: Really? In that case, you can use this.
Shiho: Huh? Is this...a coupon?
Manager: That's right. Do you know Vivid Street?
Manager: My brother opened up an instrument shop just off it. Why don't you check it out?
Shiho: I see...
Shiho: Thank you very much for the suggestion. If you're sure it's alright, I'll accept this coupon.
Manager: No problem. And good luck!
Manager: I'm looking forward to Leo/need's solo show.
Shiho: Thank you. We'll be sure to make it a great show.
Shiho: I'm going to save a bunch on repairs now... I have to thank my boss next time I see him.
Shiho: (Not to mention all those rare models they had. It was cool getting to try them all out.)
Shiho: (But none of them compared to my own bass. I've used it for so long that my fingers are just...used to it.)
Shiho: (... I kinda want to play it now. My amp's in the shop, though, so... I think I'll go over to SEKAI.)
???: ♪——————!!
Shiho: (What's that singing?)
Shiho: (They're so good... I think it's coming from this way.)
Shiho: Oh... Isn't that...?
An: Hey, we're Vivid BAD SQUAD! How are you all doing?! Are you guys having fun?!
Shiho: Yes... It's Shiraishi.
An: ♪————!! ————!!
Shiho: (I've got goosebumps. Her voice is so overwhelming...!)
Shiho: (And... My heart aches just listening to her.)
Shiho: (I already knew she had a powerful voice from when I saw her at Shibuya Festa. But she's gotten even better now...)
Shiho: ... No surprises there.
Shiho: (If I remember right, she's trying to surpass a legendary event called RAD WEEKEND.)
Shiho: (And she must be serious if she can sing this passionately... So passionately my heart aches.)
Shiho: (That's right. We'll also...)
Shiho: (Everyone's in good form.)
Shiho: (But, I keep thinking about yesterday...)
Shiho: (That overpowering voice... That was incredible.)
Shiho: (I want to try performing with that kind of power. I bet it could really profoundly resonate with people...)
Shiho: (I know. I can...heavily accent my strumming to produce a sort of clean, staccato sound...!)
Len: Wow, that was really good just now. It was like the bass picked up and pulled everything together.
MEIKO: They're on a whole new level, including their playing itself.
Shiho: Keep it up till the end!
Ichika: *Nod*
Saki: That's all eight songs covered! Nice work, everyone!
Luka: Hehe. I have to say, you've all built up stamina and improved your performance skills.
Honami: Yes, I suppose practice is paying off.
Rin: But hey! Shih was extra incredible today, right?!
MEIKO: You're right. She was producing an even cleaner sound than usual, and playing with extra feeling.
Rin: Did something good happen?!
Shiho: Not exactly... But something like that.
Len: Huh?
Shiho: There's this friend of a friend, and I got to hear her sing.
Shiho: And when I did, it was like I was charged up, or like I had a fire lit under me.
Ichika: Wow... For you to be that impressed, this person must really be incredible.
Shiho: Oh, you probably know her, Ichika. She's Kohane's teammate, Shiraishi.
Ichika: Wait, Shiraishi? So that's who it was...!
Ichika: Shiraishi is definitely talented. I learned a lot from her when she taught me about singing.
Miku: Wow... I think I'd like to hear this Shiraishi person's singing too.
Shiho: I hear she and her team are putting on their own events lately. If you're interested, wanna check one out together?
Miku: Really? I'd love the chance to go and listen.
Shiho: Got it. In that case, I'll ask Kohane next time I see her.
Saki: Kohane's helping us out so much with the flyers for the solo show, so it'd be great to all go support them!
Honami: Actually, everyone. Can we talk for a second about those flyers?
Honami: It turns out Kohane has some samples of the solo show flyer ready for us to look at.
Saki: Whoa! She already got that far with the design we asked her to make?
Honami: Yes, and I'd like to get the final product printed soon since there isn't much time left before the show. I had planned to go collect the samples this Saturday, but...
Ichika: Did something come up?
Honami: Yes, I'll be going on a family outing... I don't think I can go collect them that day.
Honami: So, it would be a big help if someone could go instead of me to collect them. Are any of you free?
Shiho: Saturday... Okay, how about I go?
Honami: Oh, are you sure?
Shiho: Yeah. My shift ends early that day, and I think I can go on the way home.
Honami: I see... Thank you, Shiho!
Shiho: So, where do I need to go?
Honami: Um, it's a place on Vivid Street called...
Shiho: Weekend Garage...
